$$
(a-1)^n + (a+1)^n \bmod{a^2}
$$
Looking for the maximum remainder.

$$
(a-1)^n + (a+1)^n =
\sum_i bin(n,i) * (-1)^{n-i} a^i
+
\sum_i bin(n,i) * a^i
$$
The only terms which don't die are
$$
(-1)^{n-1} * n * a + n * a + (-1)^n + 1
$$
If $n$ is even, this is $2$.
If $n$ is odd, this is $2na$.

Note that $a$ divides the modulus $a^2$.

**Example**.

